:: Approach the man {"position":"700,425","size":"100,100"}
All you see is a big hat and what looks from afar to be big dreadlocks coming from within. You approach and notice the dreadlocks are firmly gripping the darkened face of the creature that sits before you. The humanoid holds its face between palms, seemingly hiding it.

Will: "As if that's what he should be ashamed of."

[["Sir, do you have your coins on you?"]]
[[Stand close to him silently, breathing heavily and irregularly take a sip of your drink.]]


:: Death is benign {"position":"575,1550","size":"100,100"}
Old Man: "Nothing can be worse than this." He touches the back of his skull, strokes the dreadlocks carefully. "I disagree... If this is death... It's never-ending. It's badly written. Where is the peace they always said you got at the end? Where's the silence?"

[["No rest for the wicked."]]
[["Not here. The ship always bustles with information and whatever other nonsense that echoes through your head. You might as well get used to it. |Get used to it]]


