:: What? {"position":"700,1175","size":"100,100"}
Old Man:

Snivels. Slowly removes the hat to reveal the true nature of those strange dreadlocks. Dark green, spotted, scaly. They are definitely not dreadlocks. I can clearly see the cracks they left in the skull from when they burst out of it.

He scratches the top of his head. Mutters something under his breath.

Old Man: "What?" His eyes roll up once more. "Sir... Please. I need to go. I have to go see my daughter. Penelope. Have you seen her? I need to find her. She's lost... I... I need to find her."

[["I doubt you'll find her in here. This place is for the dead, old man."]]


